d_revise` action to revise the code and add the necessary functionality.\n3. After the code is revised, **Agent3** can be involved to optimize the code.\n\nIf you need to communicate with Agent1 to ensure they are aware of their task, you can send a follow-up message:\n\n```plaintext\nPlease ensure that the initial code framework for the NetworkGuard security system is created as per the task description. Once you have completed this, I will revise the code to add the missing functionality.\n```\n\nThis will help keep the process moving forward and ensure that each agent is aware of their responsibilities.", 'agent3': "Based on the task history and the roles assigned, the next task is for **Agent1** to create the initial code framework for the NetworkGuard security system. Once Agent1 completes this step, the code will be handed over to **Agent3** for revision and optimization.\n\nHere's a summary of the next steps:\n\n1. **Agent1's Task:**\n   - Create the initial code framework for NetworkGuard.\n   - Ensure the code includes basic functionalities for real-time monitoring, threat detection, and alerts.\n\n2. **Agent3's Task:**\n   - Once the initial code is created, Agent3 will take over to revise the code.\n   - After revision, Agent3 will optimize the code based on innovation and creativity.\n\nSince Agent1 is responsible for the initial code creation, the next action is to wait for Agent1 to complete this task and provide the initial code framework. Once that is done, you can proceed with the revision and optimization phases."}, 'task_results': [{'agent1': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": false, "error-msg": "Solution file already exists at C:\\\\Users\\\\70454\\\\Desktop\\\\PredictDesign\\\\results\\\\parallel_api_test\\\\runtime_configs\\\\coding\\\\task_55_workspace\\\\solution.py. Operation aborted."}'}, {'agent2': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": true, "message": "Code review and revision completed.